  "2026-04-03T11:59:25.339Z",codex-agent,"Wave breakdown: Wave1 Type UX (Issues 1/2/5) on pm-bzyr and pm-r15d; Wave2 Linked-file hygiene (Issues 3/4/6) on pm-ap8l; Wave3 Diff/template/search/list UX (Issues 8/9/10/12) on pm-p9z, pm-zzt1, pm-780f, pm-pmd; Wave4 Reference validation (Issues 13/14) on pm-3gi and pm-2p6q. Non-breaking constraints: preserve existing command defaults, prefer additive/opt-in flags for new behavior, keep aliases and exit-code contracts stable, and use warning-first validation where strict enforcement could break current users."
  "2026-04-03T12:29:13.548Z",codex-agent,"Implemented Wave1 type discoverability follow-up by extending type-aware help in src/cli/main.ts to include explicit type-option schema details (required marker, allowed values, aliases, description) for create/update --help --type <value>. Added integration coverage in tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts and updated README/PRD/CHANGELOG discoverability language. Evidence: pm test pm-r15d --run passed (full 722-test regression + targeted 86-test discoverability suite); pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (94.44% stmts, 91.42% branch, 96.19% funcs, 94.73% lines)."
  "2026-04-04T20:39:02.007Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence for reactivation: searched tracker for type-model and calendar UX overlap, reviewed open/in-progress queues, and confirmed this existing epic is the canonical parent for type discoverability and required-option UX continuation."
  "2026-04-04T21:12:32.418Z",codex-agent,"Epic close-out: completed reopened delta through pm-x2k0/pm-p5q3 by adding Event/Reminder/Milestone/Meeting as built-in item types and keeping required-option discoverability deterministic across CLI/help/completion surfaces. Evidence: pm test-all --status in_progress passed linked tests; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test passed (856 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (branch 91.03%)."
